The Council on Economic Advisers has released a report called "Estimates of Job Creation from the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009." This report outlines how the administration will measure the progress of creating and saving jobs under the Recovery Act. The methodology for measuring progress was developed in the early days of the administration and aims to be simple, conservative, and accurate. The model combines a macro approach based on projected and actual spending with direct reporting by recipients to improve accuracy. The report can be viewed by clicking the provided link.